    "title": "Creating screenshots of your app for localizers"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When running UI tests of your localizations, you can generate screenshots to include",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in the exported localization folders that you give to localizers. The screenshots",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "provide context for the localizable strings and resources in the interface. You can",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "generate screenshots from your project’s test plans or Test scheme.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To include the screenshots in the Xcode Localization Catalog (a folder with a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".xcloc",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "file extension), see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Xcode/documentation/Xcode/exporting-localizations",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-a-test-plan",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create a test plan",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you add many localizations to your project, test plans are ideal for generating",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "screenshots because you can create a configuration for each. A test plan (a file",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "with a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".xctestplan",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " file extension) specifies which tests to run and how to run",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "them one or more times.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can use an existing test plan or create a new one. To add a test plan, choose",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Product > Test Plan > New Test Plan in Xcode. Enter a name for the test plan and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "click Create.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you want to convert your project from using schemes to test plans, choose Product > Scheme > Convert Scheme",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to use Test Plans, select “Create Test Plan from scheme”,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "then click Convert. In the next dialog, you can change the name of the test plan,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "then click Save. The test plan appears in the editor area.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-localization-configurations",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add localization configurations",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Add a configuration for each localization to your test plan. In the Project navigator,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "select the test plan, then click Configurations. On the left, click the Add button",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "(+) at the bottom. Select the new configuration that appears and enter a name for",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the localization.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Edit the configuration file for the localization test. Under Localization, set the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Application Language and Application Region settings to the corresponding language",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and region for the localization. Under UI Testing, switch Localization Screenshots",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "from Off to On.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "creating-screenshots-of-your-app-for-localizers-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Run-tests-to-generate-screenshots",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Run tests to generate screenshots",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Next time you run your tests (choose Product > Test), Xcode saves the screenshots",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for each localization to disk. In the Test navigator, next to every screenshot, Xcode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "includes a property list (Localizable Strings Info) that maps the strings to the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "frame where the string appears in the screenshot. The property list includes the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "string IDs (that appear in the exported XLIFF file) and frame locations.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Generate-screenshots-using-schemes",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Generate screenshots using schemes",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Alternatively, if you don’t use test plans, you can make similar edits to the Test",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scheme to generate screenshots. In Xcode, choose Product > Scheme > Edit Scheme,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "click the Test scheme, then click Options. Choose the language and region from the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "pop-up menus, then select “Gather screenshots for localization.”",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
